All Peru rebels , one hostage , killed - local radio . All of the Marxist rebels and one hostage were killed after Peruvian soldiers stormed the Japanese ambassador ' s residence to free the 72 hostages , local radio reported on Tuesday . Earlier , a local television station said that all hostages were rescued alive . Among the diplomats , military officials and businessmen held hostage were Peru ' s Foreign Minister Francisco Tudela and Japanese ambassador Morihisa Aoki . 
